Huanggang: funerals, masks and diapers

Flower scales

On February 6,2020, the 13th day of the first month of the year of the Gengzi rat, on the 14th day of the city closure in Huanggang, Hubei Province.

The first thing I wake up to these days is to open the latest outbreak report. In the middle of the night, a sudden light rain dispersed a sunny day that lasted for several days, and the temperature dropped rapidly. And the numbers in the outbreak report speak in hushed tones:

There is no light. The clouds are still gathering.

My City, Huanggang, is the second city in the country after Wuhan in terms of death and disaster, with more than 1,800 new cases of pneumonia confirmed and still growing rapidly.

A few years ago, 700,000 people poured in from Wuhan, turning the city into a gun-shy place.

Road, has been exported by the original city, closed to the county between the county and county, and now to the village.

And today, I'm going to a funeral.

A funeral in a minute or five

The deceased, an 80-year-old woman in a relative's family, died three days ago of severe Alzheimer's disease, or dementia. But until this Spring Festival, she is still in the countryside taking care of her eldest son, who was maimed in a traffic accident years ago.

It's hard to imagine the two of them living side by side on a daily basis. Just like we can not imagine, or even have no time to imagine, those who are locked in Wuhan City, with how wandering, fear, confused mood of life, struggling.

Before the festival, the deceased's youngest son returned from Shenzhen to Hubei Province for the New Year and took her from her hometown to the county town to take care of her.

In Shenzhen, the younger son lives with his daughter's family and takes care of their children. Support your parents or help the next generation raise their grandchildren? Was the hardest decision of his generation, of his age.

The children are debating whether to put their mother in a nursing home, and there seems to be serious disagreement as to whether it is to be trusted, and in rural areas as much as it costs to put the elderly in a nursing home, it's a matter of pride, Florida, though the elderly may be better cared for.

But the old man died before the conclusion could be reached.

I heard that the old man's symptoms are intermittent, sometimes he will know someone, sometimes he will remember something.

Just before she died, she was packing up at home. The daughter-in-law saw this and asked her what she was doing. She replied that a member of staff had spoken to her about going to a nursing home and was waiting downstairs in her car to pick her up. Daughter-in-law asks her: Do you have money? The old man said, I do. Then he felt in his pocket and sat down gloomily: I have no money.

There was no one waiting for her downstairs, of course.

When I heard this, I suddenly felt that this was the last time the old man would help his children to cope -- although, at this point, burying her was a real problem.

Hearing relatives call from the county to inform the elderly soon, the first is shocked, did not expect so soon. Then the family said:

It's not a good time to die.

That is a pity, of course. After all, no one really thinks "when is the right time to die" .

What we regret is that, on the one hand, people are going through a plague, and the hardship of living has taken away some of the grief of death, and on the other hand, in these difficult times, the inconvenience of transportation, etc. , the custom of paying a decent burial to a countryman will not be realized.

80-year-old people, did not suffer much pain in death, in many places is a matter of joy, commonly known as joy. Huanggang itself is no exception. Normally, there are grand funerals, followed by several days of feasting, drama and pomp.

But now, with the outbreak fast-growing, Huanggang has already imposed the toughest controls, closing roads everywhere and banning non-essential people from going out. At this critical time, mass funerals are strictly forbidden.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Local banners

According to the original custom, the old man died in the county seat, but did not die in his hometown, need to send back to his hometown first, after holding various ceremonies to be buried. And now it's just a matter of keeping it simple.

The town's old family brought in a funeral procession, which was still willing to start work, to help carry the coffin that the old man had already prepared to the ancestral grave hill, and to preside over the next burial; the family in the county town hired a car, pull the old man's body to the ancestral grave hill.

The two sides meet directly on the mountain and complete the burial.

There are currently more than 100 confirmed cases in our county, more than half of which live in the county seat. And our town is one of the few places where we haven't seen an outbreak. Before departure, the county's families need to go to the local police station issued a vehicle pass. This is the only way other than official vehicles can be driven on the road.

And it's this pass that's GonNa help us in another way.

People from the county, and people from the township, meet on this special occasion. Although all are relatives, relatively know-it-all, even if there is no plan to hold a banquet, but there will inevitably be communication. The huge uncertainty, and the lingering local infection cloud for days, remain troubling.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The small talk before the funeral, people unconsciously stand very far away

My father-in-law and I were the only representatives of the family, and there were not even 20 people on the scene, plus all the people who did the work. Everyone mouth said "special period, special treatment" , the heart with a great regret and the elderly to make a final farewell.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Relatives and friends lined up to pay their respects

In the chilly wind and spring rain, in the smoke rising from the cemetery, in the low chanting of the master, in the mournful chant of the grave digger, an old man who has lived here for more than 80 years and never left forever rests in this land.

After sending their parents home for the New Year, the family of the elder's granddaughter, the daughter of the younger son, returned to Shenzhen as planned before the closure of the city in Huanggang, where they have been voluntarily quarantined. Now, grandma unexpectedly died suddenly, but they can not come back to see the old man, or send the old man a journey. And I, an out-of-towner who's only been here twice, am a witness.

This is a rural Hubei style, but there is no parade, no banquet, no party, no Suona and singing, not even crying, no sad, silent funeral.

And the whole funeral, it wasn't even five minutes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
2. Face Masks

Before planning this funeral, we discovered a serious problem -- we were out of masks -- as if it wasn't a N95, or a disposable mask.

The mask before, or last December before the road closure from the county opened a pharmacy relatives bought spare. Even then, no one would have thought it would come to this.

Although in the friend circle and the WECHAT group, everyone has been trying to find a way to search for masks, complaining about face masks being limited to purchase, requisitioned, and even intercepted. But previously, living in a rural home does not need to go out often, masks are not so important, many people even wear masks to play outside, chat.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fewer and fewer people are playing after they run out of masks

And we, when the refrigerator in our house became empty, realized that although there were vegetables and radishes in the vegetable field, there were children and old people in the house, so we had to go out and buy some meat.

By the way, get some face masks.

But when I drove on the road, I found that the village entrance had been closed. There was a pharmacy on the nearest shabby shopping street and a health clinic in the village, but, as expected, they were out of stock.

And we, two of the masks we went out to buy, were useless. The jokes on the Internet became real, and when a black comedy happened to me, I realized what I had to do.

We're getting anxious. What about the funeral? The bigger question is: What if you don't have a mask on the way back to Shenzhen, even though it's far away?

At this point, little sister's classmates told her that there are some masks in stock at home can be given to us. But Express delivery, traffic has long been interrupted, the original drive only half an hour more than 20 km road, now is out of reach.

Fortunately, starting two days ago, every household in the village will be given a uniform distribution of two disposable masks. After two days, we decided to go out with two layers of disposable masks each.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It is very square to take this out in the center of the epidemic area

As the funeral approached, another way to get a mask came to mind -- A passport.

At this time, the county road has been separated. Little sister's classmates hard to hand over the mask to a relative's hands, and then relatives will mask to the funeral site, hand over to us.

50 disposable masks. It's been a long time coming.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
And we finally have some face masks.

3. Diapers

In the first article, "Huanggang: Spring Festival in the deputy center of the epidemic area, " he described our record of returning from Shenzhen to Huanggang, Hubei Province, for the Lunar New Year. We brought home a year and a half's worth of content that had been empathetic to some new parents, and many of our friends asked if we needed help. In it I wrote:

"before we went back to Hubei, we had planned to go back in 10 days. Kid's got the most stuff, a trunk full of'em. But the two most important consumables, diapers and milk powder, are used less and less every day. At the moment, the milk powder lasts a month at the most, and the diaper could last less than 10 days."

Now the diapers are completely used up, and back to the deep long-term.

We've been preparing for this for a long time.

First of all, we checked something on the treasure, diaper direct order is OK, but the time of delivery to Huanggang is uncertain. Given our knowledge of the roads, it almost certainly wouldn't make sense to wait until after the closures were lifted to deliver the goods.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
So, we decided to take the "curve to save the country" strategy: The wife is the staff of SF, it is said that the company can still send express to Hubei. So we decided to buy diapers from something to send to a friend's home in Shenzhen, and then ask him to help send here. SF express picked up the order and sent it to the cargo plane.

The latest arrival time given by SF express was 12:00 on the 31st of January. On February 1, the package arrived at Ezhou Airport, less than 200 kilometers from here.

But by February 3rd, it was still being sent to Ezhou, where it had been suspended for two days; after 12 o'clock, it did not arrive, and was instead delivered at 18 o'clock.

After 18:00, the delivery information was finally updated and the latest estimated delivery time became: Nil.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After 2-1, the courier information stopped updating

At this point, we only have a day's supply of diapers left, and we don't even have an alternative.

So, on that trip to find a mask, we tried to buy some homemade diapers -- it's all in town, but it's better than nothing.

But it was not until we went out that we realized that the road was closed to the village and we could not get to the town.

However, we found the only small supermarket near the village that was open, and found something called a diaper.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Any parent would understand our trepidation: we've never heard of the brand, we don't know if our kids are allergic; we've never used it, we don't even know how to fix it.

Posted to a friend circle, a friend told US how to use: a waist band of rubber band. A friend asked if we needed any help, even though it was hard for us to get any.

But in these tough times, it's nice to have someone with you, someone who cares about how you feel.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
His wife contacted the local head of SF express and learned that the courier had actually arrived in the county seat. We had expected to be able to use that precious vehicle pass, ask relatives will be back with diapers.

But SF express can only deliver to certain designated places in the county seat, and the most critical issue is that they are still applying to the local authorities for delivery permission.

Despite the efforts of many contacts, found the location of the courier and contact, but the time, space barrier finally let our plan fall through. After several communications, the diapers were handed over to the second sister, who lives in the county seat, and we would probably have to wait until the final release to get them.

We found that the water absorption capacity of children's diapers is much worse than the previous King of flowers. Just then, the owner of the formerly closed town supermarket sent a message:

"You have a neighbor coming to buy milk powder. Do you want to wear a diaper? "

The neighbor, unable to go to the village committee because his child had run out of milk powder, went to great pains to print a certificate report before being allowed to buy milk powder in the nearest town. And because we had contacted the supermarket owner before, he inadvertently asked the neighbors from where, it is the first time we think.

Yes! Yes! Of course!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
When we were picking out diapers for our kids, we tried a lot of brands, we read a lot of reviews, and we ran a lot of places to find the perfect one.

In fact, not only diaper, including milk powder, lotion, toys and everything, as novice parents always try to give the best to their children. In this process will pay a lot of effort to select and prepare.

However, even though there weren't a lot of options this time around, we were still buying brands we hadn't heard of or wouldn't even consider before.

But when we finally get the diaper, open the moment, our mood is extremely relaxed. Then pick up the baby, as you have done so many times before, and say happily:

Come on, let's go change your diaper.

4. epilogue

A special funeral, a special pass, a special time mask, and a special time diaper come together in this magical moment, connecting the whole world:

The dead are dying, the living are living, the young are growing.

These things, compared with the tragic events in the blockaded city of Wuhan, are The Imaginary Invalid; compared with the people who have suffered great economic losses, we can even get along with our families with ease for a long time.

I still believe that there is no such thing as true empathy. All joys and sorrows are true only if experienced by oneself.

Because people seek their own survival, and have no time for the suffering and difficulties of others. But when the same pain and fear suddenly strikes, and everyone may not be spared, there is a precious opportunity for empathy:

What happened to me wasn't because of who I was or what I did. We just happen to be in a place at a time like this, in a place like Florida, and it happens to everyone.

Although that feeling is still not profound enough, we finally have an opportunity to put ourselves in the shoes of others and think about their suffering.

A sudden disaster, let us start thinking about the meaning of life. We didn't have time to grieve, to feel bad, or even to say goodbye. But when all this is over, all the people who survived deserve to grow up the way they did.

Some psychologists say that panic is natural, but people instinctively protect themselves under pressure. Instead, after a disaster, people's psychological problems may focus on the outbreak.

For example, the funeral, the "neglect" of the deceased caused by the guilt; or, for the living, and not to seek a way of life.

But now, behind the mourners in the cemetery, in the silent rain before the eyes of relatives and friends, in the sound of firecrackers through the clouds, in overcoming difficulties to get all kinds of supplies, I began to think seriously:

What is true heroism?

Despite knowing in advance that many things are impossible to achieve, many difficulties are impossible to overcome. But when we have to do something for our loved ones anyway, to keep them from getting stuck, we don't think about the consequences of holding on, trying, trying, and never giving up hope.

Perhaps this is the kind of "recognize the truth of life after still love life" spirit bar.

Before, mother-in-law planted a red plum tree in the yard of her hometown. This year for the first time the little grandson home for the New Year, people are very surprised, the red plum tree hung full of flowers and bones for the first time. We laughed and said the flowers would bloom when the little grandson returned to the city.

At that time, no one thought we would stay here so long, or even really can wait for the flowers to bloom. Sustainable cold wind and cold rain, flower bud is still flower bud, is still late not open.

But above, flocks of migrating birds have begun to fly north. It is widely believed that:

Spring will come and the red plums will bloom.
